properties.Name: DistributionMethod
properties.Description:
The method by which Life Insurance benefits are to be distributed to a person's descendants.

Ex:
- Per Capita
- Per Stripes

PER CAPITA
Death benefits from a life insurance policy are divided equally among the  living primary beneficiaries.

PER STRIPES
Death benefits are divided equally among the  named beneficiaries.

Should a named beneficiary be deceased, his or her share than goes to the  living descendants of that individual.
